laboratory_examinations.findings: Dilated, fluid-filled appendix in the right lower quadrant measuring 8 mm in maximum diameter with surrounding fat stranding and mucosal hyper-enhancement. No focal air or fluid to suggest microperforation or evidence of abscess. An appendicolith is noted in the appendiceal tip. The liver enhances homogeneously without perfusion defect or focal liver lesion. Normal findings for gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, bilateral adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, duodenum, and intra-abdominal loops of small and large bowel. No hydronephrosis or suspicious renal lesion. No free air or ascites present.
